<a name="minblocklen"></a>
<h3> Minimal Block Length </h3>
<div>A SimShiftDB alignments is composed of (possibly) multiple ungapped alignments (called blocks). This parameter\
s sets the minimal length such an alignment has to achieve not to be discarded. Raising this parameter result in a faster run, whereas lowering this parameter increases sensitivity.

<a name="localevaluecut"> </a>
<h3> Local Evalue Cutoff</h3>
E-Value Cutoff for local alignments from the first step of the algorithms.

<a name="evaluecut"></a>
<h3>E-Value Cutoff</h3>
Defines the E-Value an alignment has to achieve to be included in the output file.

<a name="output"></a>
<h3>Output Format</h3>
Residue Output:  SimShift standard output <br>
Full Alignment Output: This is not the alignment output decribed here but a straightforward fasta-like global alignment output.
</div>
